<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 10:45PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Moore,
northwestern Sampson, southwestern Harnett, Cumberland and northern
Hoke Counties through 1130 PM EDT...
At 1045 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pope AFB, or near Fort Bragg, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Southern Pines, Fort Bragg, Pinehurst, Aberdeen,
Godwin, Pope AFB, Spring Lake, Eastover and Stedman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
